PRINTING CODE. Amendments: Whenever an existing statute (or a section of the Indiana
Constitution) is being amended, the text of the existing provision will appear in this style type,
additions will appear in this style type, and deletions will appear in this style type.
Additions: Whenever a new statutory provision is being enacted (or a new constitutional
provision adopted), the text of the new provision will appear in this style type. Also, the
word NEW will appear in that style type in the introductory clause of each SECTION that adds
a new provision to the Indiana Code or the Indiana Constitution.
Conflict reconciliation: Text in a statute in this style type or this style type reconciles conflicts
between statutes enacted by the 2025 Regular Session of the General Assembly.
HOUSE BILL No. 1213
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning
taxation.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 6-2.5-4-5, AS AMENDED BY P.L.137-2022,
2 SECTION 19, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
3 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 5. (a) A power subsidiary or a person engaged as
4 a public utility is a retail merchant making a retail transaction when the
5 subsidiary or person furnishes or sells electrical energy, natural or
6 artificial gas, water, steam, or steam heating service to a person for
7 commercial or domestic consumption.
8 (b) A power subsidiary or a person engaged as a public utility
9 is not a retail merchant making a retail transaction when the
10 subsidiary or person furnishes or sells electrical energy, natural or
11 artificial gas, water, steam, or steam heating service to a person for
12 domestic consumption.
13 SECTION 2. [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026] (a) IC 6-2.5-4-5, as
14 amended by this act, applies only to retail transactions occurring
15 after June 30, 2026.
16 (b) Except as provided in subsection (c), a retail transaction is
17 considered to have occurred after June 30, 2026, if the property
2026 IN 1213—LS 6023/DI 134

2
1 whose transfer constitutes selling at retail is delivered to the
2 purchaser or to the place of delivery designated by the purchaser
3 after June 30, 2026.
4 (c) Notwithstanding the delivery of the property constituting
5 selling at retail after June 30, 2026, a transaction is considered to
6 have occurred before July 1, 2026, to the extent that:
7 (1) the agreement of the parties to the transaction is entered
8 into before July 1, 2026; and
9 (2) payment for the property furnished in the transaction is
10 made before July 1, 2026.
11 (d) This SECTION expires January 1, 2029.
